column9:
MoU: 1. Exchange of faculty members, research scholars & students;
2. Exchange of lectures/presentations, scientific materials, publications, and information;
3. Joint research activities and publications, conferences, academic programs, and cultural activities;
4. Joint research projects and joint course of study.

MoU: a. Learning and teaching including the development of a programme leading to an award;
b. Exchange of students for a given period through a recognised exchange programme;
c. Exchange of faculty members of the universities;
d. Exchange of lectures/presentations via video teleconference activities; including scientific materials, publications, and information;
e. Co-ordination through their respective offices in joint or collaborative research projects.

MoU: a) Develop academic and cultural interchange in areas of education;
b) Faculty and student exchange; 
c) Exchange of scholarly materials and information;
d) Participation in joint or collaborative research projects and grants;
e) Establishment of arrangement for students to complete their course of study and graduate at the partner’s institution, provided all conditions and standards for admission and respective programs are fulfilled.

MoU: a. academic study and research opportunities, and faculty-sponsored practical training assignments for students;
b. student exchange;
c. exchange of academic materials and information regarding programs of study, conferences, and other professional activities ;
d. exchange ofprofessors and other colleagues to teach, collaborate in research and publication, and engage in other professional activities; and
e. collaboration in any other way that is considered mutually beneficial.

LoI: (a) Educational programs and trainings for enhancing e-Learning competencies;
(b) Academic Exchange;
(c) Research and Development of e-Learning contents;
(d) Joint operation of e-Learning courses and short-term courses;
(e) Leverage e-Learning content;
(f) Co-utilization of e-Learning content; and
(g) Other projects necessary for achieving the purpose of this agreement.

MoU: • Joint teaching activities; 
• Exchange of faculty members;
• Exchange of students;
• Study Abroad opportunities (Fee paying); and
• Professional development of staff.

MoU:
(a) Collaborative research projects;
(b) Joint academic and related activities;
(c) Staff exchange for teaching and research activities;
(d) Student exchange to undertake study or participate in research programes; and
(e) Any other collaborative activities as mutually agreed in writing between the Parties.

MoU:
a) Exchange of faculty, lecturers, and researchers and other research and administrative staff;
b) Exchange of students;
c) Conduct of collaborative research projects;
d) Conduct of lectures and organizing of symposia;
e) Exchange of academic information and materials;
f) Promotion of other cooperative opportunities as mutually agreed.

MoU: a. Encouraging visits by faculty members from one university to the other for the purpose of engaging in research, teaching, or other educational activities;
b. Supporting the exchange of undergraduate, graduate and doctoral students for study and research;
c. Facilitating the exchange of non-academic staff for exchange experiences;
d. Fostering the exchange of academic publications and scholarly information; and
e. Promoting joint research activities and other academic activities that are of mutual interest and that enhance the above-mentioned goals.

MoA: a. Guest lectures;
b. Student mobility and faculty/satff mobility;
c. Adjunct Professorship; and
d. Short programs/summer school.

MoU: (a) exchange of faculty members, research scholars and students with credit transfer programs;
(b) exchange of lectures/presentations via video teleconference activities; including scientific materials, publications, and information;
(c) joint research activities and publications, conferences, academic programs, and cultural activities;
(d) joint research projects and joint courses of study, with particular emphasis on internationally funded projects;
(e) collaboration in organizing seminar, conferences, symposiums lectures and intellectual discourse;
(f) special short-duration academic programs and others as appropriate, and
(g) any others areas of co-operation to be mutually agreed upon by the parties.

MoU: a) Develop academic and cultural exchange in education;
b) Faculty and student exchange; 
c) Exchange of scholarly materials and information;
d) Participation in joint or collaborative research projects and grants application;
e) Articulation arrangement for students to complete their course of study provided all conditions and standards for admission and respective programs are fulfilled.

MoU:
a) Exchange of faculty, lecturers, and researchers and other research and administrative staff;
b) Exchange of students;
c) Conduct of collaborative research projects;
d) Conduct of lectures and organizing of symposia;
e) Exchange of academic information and materials;
f) Promotion of other cooperative opportunities as mutually agreed.

MoU:
i) Student exchange programmes; 
ii) Academic staff exchange programmes; 
iii) Summer school arrangements for students; 
iv) Internship or Research Placements for students;
v) Joint Professor supervision of student projects/theses/research works;
vi) Research collaboration;
vii) Program benchmarking exercises.

MoU:
a) Mutual exchange of students; 
b) Mutual exchange of researchers; 
c) Joint development of teaching contents and examination regulations;
d) Joint scientific publications;
e) Mutual support for the joint implementation of externally funded projects;
f) Mutual support in the preparation of final theses.

MoU: a. Exploration of cultural exchange programs between China - Indonesia:
i. Hunan City University will accept the students from PCU to learn Chinese language in the campus of Hunan City University;
ii. Exploration of international Chinese education cooperation program.
b. Exploration of collaborative programs in teaching and academic:
i. Student exchanges;
ii. Faculty/staff exchanges;
iii. Organizing joint academic activities such as seminars, lectures, conferences and establishment of international laboratories;
iv. Exchange of academic materials and other information of common interest.

MoU:
1. Research collaboration for projects, papers, patents & funding proposals;
2. Student internship programs; 
3. Joint technical workshops and/or seminars; 
4. Student exchange program (SEP) & faculty exchange program (FEP)
5. Collaborative national and international conferences.

MoU:
1. Exchanging students, researchers and academic staff within the frame of Erasmus+ or/and individual agreements;
2. Developing and supporting joint dual diploma programs;
3. Participation/organization of conferences and publication of scientific proceedings;
4. Reviewing scientific publications, dissertations, and other research papers;
5. Exchanging information about seminars and scientific conferences organized by both Parties;
6. Applying for and participating in joint research projects;
7. Implementing mutual internship programs;
8. Supporting the establishment and functioning of language lectorates;
 9. Exchange of information and documentation, including methodical recommendations, scientific publications and research results.
10. Other academic and research activities that could contribute the development of higher education in both countries.

MoU:
a) Promote mutually beneficial and complementary academic and technological cooperation programmes between both parties.
b) Arrangements are made for teachers and researchers to visit, exchange, give short-term lectures, or conduct research in the other party; Both parties will organize exchange visits, exchanges, and short-term study programmes for their students;
c) Jointly organized academic seminars and research lectures;
d) Both parties will cooperate to develop a platform for technological innovation in the relevant areas of cooperation

MoU:
I. Student, Faculty/Staff Mobility
a. Physical, virtual, and hybrid forms of mobility;
b. Twinning, Joint Degree and Dual Degree programs.

II. Research and Development
a. Joint supervision and joint research and research projects;
b. Resource sharing (research infrastructure software, and human experties);
c. Events, workshops, symposiums/conferences;
d. Publication, intellectual property (IP), and technology commercialization.

III. Innovation and Entrepreneurship
a. Seminars, workshops, conferences and programs;
b. Joint hackathons, ideathons, B-plan competitions, etc.;
c. Joint physical, virtual, or hybrid programs in innovation and entrepreneurship;
d. Joint innovation projects;
e. Establishing start-up to start-up connections;
f. Establishing incubator-to-incubator connections.

MoU: 1. Active utilization of the information-providing application for international students, "DAGACHI I";
2. Mutual positive promotional activities and support for each Party through the "DAGACHI" application and various media channels;
3. Active promotion and dissemination of information and activities related to International students provided by each Party;
4. Continuous provision of relevant data between the Parties.

MoU:
a. Student exchange, including cultural and educational programs, on-the-job-training, internship program, and service learning or volunteering opportunities;
b. Unversity faculty, staff, and researchers' exchange
c. Sharing library holdings;
d. Academic collaboration, including summer school, educational-tourism projects, and visiting lecturers;
e. Joint Research projects, including conferences, seminars, workshops, joint international conferences and meetings, and publications of researchers;
f. Exchange of academic information, materials, and publications;
g. Other exchange of academics and cultural nature agreed upon by both parties
